The laughs, the love and the friendship in this short film were amazing.

Before this short film came into my life, I was nothing but a mere foot massager for Charli and Dixie D'Amileo; I was underpaid, overworked and exhausted.

But after I saw this, my life did a complete 180. I felt like I had taken fourteen shots of five hour energy, and been injected with medical grade black market cocaine.

I quit my day job, and followed my dream of making Fortnite edits and uploading them to punjabi movie pirating sites.

Thank you, Tyler Hurd.

Upon downloading this, I had no true expectations. I lived with a cynical outlook on life with no real true hope for the future. I was barely surviving my day to day job as porn set janitor and I was about done with my life. I was, as many would call, a lost cause, a bad apple, someone with no reason to live nor anyone to help him out of the dark hole which I had dug myself into. Upon viewing the piece, I was overwhelmed with the spiritual and emotional power that it carried. I realized the true purpose of what it means to be human, to be loved.  I never thought that something so simple, so basic to human nature, could be so compelling, so moving. I understnad that this game may not have the popularity it trully deserves, but all I know is that this game has completly changed my outlook on my life for the better, and that it got me through a dark time and saved me from the depressive state that plagued my life for so long. Thank you, for creating one of the most amazing cinimatic and inspirational game/movie I have ever come across.
